		  	<p class="our-first-text-prop">Writing is a tough job, for real. We usually write for ourselves and share them with the world, without anyone’s approval. Ever since we started working here at Cast India, the real meaning of approvals came to light. How one approval can make you the happiest person. Being inclined towards the creative writing, the past few months were challenging, as working on technical writing mostly. Not that its boring (maybe it is a little), we surely learnt a whole lot of technical terms. But technical writing wasn’t as challenging as it’s thought it would be, compared to the content writing that had to be done for a client. It was our very First client! We had to make the most out of this opportunity and also, because it was our first client, we had to make this relationship a memorable one. You know, it was the “first impression is the last impression” sort of thing. Oh boy, content writing is TOUGH. Our writers were novice to content writing too. We had this anxiousness going on inside, everyone was facing it differently. Maybe it was because we had made ourselves comfortable with technical writing or that we just couldn’t picture the company well, it was eating us up. After having a good session of chat with sir and sharing our thoughts with him, it led us to a fresh new start. We researched, scribbled, doodled, danced about and just did almost everything that could inspire us to start penning our thoughts. Once we gathered, we started pouring down our thoughts, we didn’t stop and that’s when we realised that the gears were finally moving. Guess, we still needed a little bit of oiling to be done. With a little spice here and there, our work was finally approved!! What a relief! One of our colleagues, Radhika, updated the others about the final product, and we in that moment realised the amount of hard work and energy that everyone put in and the happiness of getting approved by the client had just brought a nonperishing smile on everyone’s face. These are the photos of that day, when the packaging was being cut out, how much fun we had! We still remember this day crystal clear and what our sir had said, “The proudest moment will be when you look at your work in the stores or on billboards or somewhere, no matter how big or small, that one accomplishment’s feelings cannot be described.” We surely felt those words inside our bones. If this is what accomplishment feels like for one client, we’re ready to take on more clients! Here’s to our first client and many more …</p>
