		  	<p class="first-bday-cbdt-text-prop">We usually work on the 1st and the 3rd Saturday and luckily, Radhika’s birthday was also on a Saturday! It was just another ordinary yet special day. We greeted her and went back to work. Radhika wanted to leave early as it was her special day but when sir blatantly said no, we were a little disheartened. All day long the atmosphere felt dull and gloomy. But then, something unexpected happened! A surprise birthday party!! None of us saw this coming, and usually we go to the office terrace to eat lunch. Turns out, our sir had arranged for a cake, without anyone of us even getting to know he had planned all this and Radhika had called for some pizzas. Radhika was surely touched by such a warm gesture. On Monday when we were back to office, we got to know about another unexpected surprise! And once again our sir was the one, because of whom the second surprise party was possible. Sir was asked to keep Radhika back as her brother was preparing for her birthday party at home! A double surprise! Birthday or not, we all share a strong and indescribable bond. Our office is and will always a home away from home.</p>
